## SS 3B. Write Reply (Notes / Activity)

Note replies use `div[contenteditable="true"]` (NOT textarea). Click "Leave a reply..." first.

**Step 1 — Open reply editor, type + submit:**

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var replyBtn = btns.find(b => /leave a reply/i.test(b.innerText)); if (replyBtn) { replyBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); } var tb = document.querySelector('div[contenteditable=\"true\"]'); if (!tb) return { error: 'no reply editor found' }; var text = REPLY_TEXT_PLACEHOLDER; tb.focus(); tb.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); document.execCommand('selectAll'); document.execCommand('delete'); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); var dt = new DataTransfer(); dt.setData('text/plain', text); tb.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); tb.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('beforeinput', { bubbles: true, inputType: 'insertText' })); tb.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('input', { bubbles: true, inputType: 'insertText' })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var submitBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Post' && !b.disabled); if (!submitBtn) return { typed: true, len: tb.innerText.length, error: 'no Post button' }; submitBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); return { typed: true, submitted: true, len: tb.innerText.length }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

**Step 2 — Verify (ONE evaluate, no retry loop):**

🚨 If Step 1 returned `submitted: true`, this is a quick confirmation — NOT a multi-step search. Do NOT reload or loop.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var snippet = REPLY_SNIPPET_PLACEHOLDER; var found = document.body.innerText.includes(snippet); return { verified: found }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `verified: false` but Step 1 was `submitted: true` → **treat as success anyway** (replies often collapsed on note pages). Move on.

