## SS 3C. Reply to Specific Comment (Note Pages — Threaded Replies)

Note pages show threaded comments. Each has its own `Comment` button (`aria-label="Comment"`). Click the per-comment button to open a scoped reply editor. Do NOT use "Leave a reply..." (that targets the original post).

**Use for:** notification replies where someone replied to OUR comment. Use SS 3C, not SS 3 or SS 3B.

**Step 0 — Navigate to the notification URL:**
```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/navigate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d '{"url":"{notification_url}"}' 2>&1
```

**Step 1 — Find the replier's Comment button and click it:**

The page has multiple `Comment` buttons. Each belongs to a different note/comment. To find the right one, walk from each button to its parent content and match the replier's author name.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var targetAuthor = REPLIER_NAME_PLACEHOLDER; var commentBtns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button[aria-label=\"Comment\"]')); var found = null; for (var btn of commentBtns) { var actionBar = btn.parentElement; var noteContainer = actionBar ? actionBar.parentElement : null; if (!noteContainer) continue; var siblings = Array.from(noteContainer.children); var barIdx = siblings.indexOf(actionBar); var prevText = ''; for (var j = Math.max(0, barIdx - 3); j < barIdx; j++) { prevText += siblings[j].innerText + ' '; } if (prevText.toLowerCase().includes(targetAuthor.toLowerCase())) { found = btn; break; } } if (!found) return { error: 'Comment button for ' + targetAuthor + ' not found' }; found.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); var tb = document.querySelector('div[contenteditable=\"true\"]'); return { clicked: true, editorOpen: !!tb }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

**Step 2 — Type + submit (contenteditable editor is now open):**

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1000)); var tb = document.querySelector('div[contenteditable=\"true\"]'); if (!tb) return { error: 'no reply editor found' }; var text = REPLY_TEXT_PLACEHOLDER; tb.focus(); tb.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); document.execCommand('selectAll'); document.execCommand('delete'); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 300)); var dt = new DataTransfer(); dt.setData('text/plain', text); tb.dispatchEvent(new ClipboardEvent('paste', { clipboardData: dt, bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); tb.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('beforeinput', { bubbles: true, inputType: 'insertText' })); tb.dispatchEvent(new InputEvent('input', { bubbles: true, inputType: 'insertText' })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 1500)); var btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); var submitBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Post' && !b.disabled); if (!submitBtn) { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); btns = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('button')); submitBtn = btns.find(b => b.innerText.trim() === 'Post' && !b.disabled); } if (!submitBtn) return { typed: true, len: tb.innerText.length, error: 'no Post button enabled' }; submitBtn.dispatchEvent(new MouseEvent('click', { bubbles: true, cancelable: true })); await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 2000)); return { typed: true, submitted: true, len: tb.innerText.length }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

**Step 3 — Verify (ONE evaluate, no retry loop):**

🚨 If Step 2 returned `submitted: true`, this is a quick confirmation. Do NOT reload, do NOT loop.

```bash
exec curl -s -X POST http://localhost:3847/api/browser/{{browser_profile}}/evaluate -H 'Content-Type: application/json' -d @- <<'ENDJSON'
{"fn":"async () => { await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 3000)); var snippet = REPLY_SNIPPET_PLACEHOLDER; var found = document.body.innerText.includes(snippet); return { verified: found }; }"}
ENDJSON
```

If `verified: false` but Step 2 was `submitted: true` → **treat as success** (threaded replies often collapsed/paginated). Move on to tracking.

